eive telephone contact from us with information regarding orders they have placed online.Correcting This InformationUpon request we provide site visitors with access to unique identifier information (e.g., customer number or password) that we maintain about them, transaction information (e.g., dates on which customers made purchases, amounts, and types of purchases) that we maintain about them, and contact information (e.g., name, address, phone number) that we maintain about them. Consumers can access this information by calling us at (212) 274-0343, ext. 11 or emailing us at membership@poets.org. You can also send us a letter at the address listed at the bottom of this page.Upon request we offer visitors the ability to have inaccuracies corrected in contact information and unique identifiers. Consumers can have this information corrected by calling us at (212) 274-0343, ext. 11 or emailing us at membership@poets.org. You can also send us a letter at the address listed at the bottom of this page.CookiesWe use cookies to store visitors preferences and to record session information, such as items that consumers add to their shopping cart.Opting OutYou may unsubscribe from our newsletters at any time by clicking on the link that says \"unsubscribe here.\" You may also let us know that you do not want to receive email from us in the future, by sending us an email at academy@poets.org, calling (212) 274-0343, or sending a letter to the address listed at the bottom of this page.Updates to This PolicyIf our information practices change at some time in the future we will post the policy changes to our website to notify you of these changes and we will use for these new purposes only data collected from the time of the policy change forward. If you are concerned about how your information is used, please visit our website periodically.SecurityWhen we transfer and receive certain types of sensitive information such as a donor's financial information, we redirect visitors to a secure server that ensures the safe transfer of sensitive credit card information by having strong SSL settings and encyption measures in place. We do not retain sensitive authentication data, such as card validation code, or personal identification number (PIN) information, in our database. We have appropriate security measures in place in our physical facility to protect against the loss, misues, or alteration of information that we have collected from you at our site.\u00a0If you feel that this site is not following its stated information policy, please email at academy@poets.org, call (212) 274-0343, or send a letter to the address listed at the bottom of this page.Mailing AddressAcademy of American Poets75 Maiden Lane, Ste. 901New York, NY 10038Phone: (212) 274-0343Email: academy@poets.org"}</script>
